{"id":17935,"date":"2014-01-29T09:15:33","date_gmt":"2014-01-29T05:15:33","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=17935"},"modified":"2021-09-07T22:54:27","modified_gmt":"2021-09-07T18:54:27","slug":"prophet-twice-fever","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/29\/prophet-twice-fever\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Fever: The Prophet afflicted with twice as much fever"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: I entered the home of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, while he was suffering from fever. I said, &#8220;O Messenger of Allah, you are suffering from a strong fever.&#8221; The Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Yes, for I am afflicted with fever like two men among you<\/strong>.&#8221; I said, &#8220;Is it that you have a double reward?&#8221; The Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>Yes, it is so. Likewise,<\/strong> <strong>t<\/strong><b>here is no Muslim who is afflicted with pain as much as the prick of a thorn, or more, but that Allah will expiate his sins, just as leaves fall from a tree<\/b>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5648, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2571<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Muttafaqun Alayhi&nbsp;<\/i><\/b>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062f\u064e\u062e\u064e\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0648\u064e\u0647\u064f\u0648\u064e \u064a\u064f\u0648\u0639\u064e\